{{use DMY dates|date=November 2016}} '''Subroto''' (born 19 September 1923)<ref>http://geomagz.geologi.esdm.go.id/subroto-dedikasi-untuk-energi/</ref><ref>http://figure.108jakarta.com/1970/09/prof-dr-subroto</ref><ref>https://m.sangattatimes.com/read/33797/20170929/182934/badak-lng-raih-subroto-award-2017/</ref> is an [[Indonesia]]n [[Administrator of the Government|administrator]] and economist. He was a doctoral graduate and faculty member of [[University of Indonesia]] between 1956 and 1963, Minister of Energy and Natural Resources between 1978 and 1988, and [[Secretary General of OPEC]] between 1988 and 1994, nearly double the tenure of his longest-serving predecessor in that position.<ref>{{cite web |title=Secretaries General of OPEC 1961–2008 |url=http://www.opec.org/opec_web/static_files_project/media/downloads/50th_anniversary/Secretaries_General.pdf |publisher=OPEC |accessdate=30 November 2016}}</ref> Like [[Indonesian names#Indonesian naming system|many Indonesians]], Subroto is known by just a single name.
